-- =*=*=*=*=*=*=*=*=*=*=*=*=*=*=*=*=*=*=*=*=*=*=*=*=*=*=*=*=*=*=*=*=*=*=*=*=*=*=*=*=*=*=*=*=*=*=*=*=*=*=*=*=*=*=*=
-- Author:		Vincent D'Souza
-- Create date: February 13, 2023
-- Description:	Returns TRUE (1) or FALSE (0) based on the CallNumber exist for an Account Code AND AllowDuplicateCallNumber flag
-- =*=*=*=*=*=*=*=*=*=*=*=*=*=*=*=*=*=*=*=*=*=*=*=*=*=*=*=*=*=*=*=*=*=*=*=*=*=*=*=*=*=*=*=*=*=*=*=*=*=*=*=*=*=*=*=
CREATE FUNCTION [dbo].udf_IsCallNumberExistForAccountCode
	( @AccountCodeId INT
	, @CallNumber VARCHAR(255)
	) 
RETURNS BIT
AS
	BEGIN
		DECLARE @IsDuplicateCallNumberAllowed INT

		SELECT @IsDuplicateCallNumberAllowed = COUNT(CallNumber)
			FROM  [ETPS2_APD].CM_Calls WITH (NOLOCK) 
		WHERE CallNumber = @CallNumber 
			AND AccountCodeID_FK = @AccountCodeID
			AND AllowDuplicateCallNumber = 0

		RETURN IIF(@IsDuplicateCallNumberAllowed > 1, 1, 0)
	END
function.name: udf_IsCallNumberExistForAccountCode

CREATE PROCEDURE [dbo].AU_RepDocuSignInfobyRepIdESignatureUserGet
  @username varchar(50) 
/***************************************************************************
OBJECT NAME			: dbo.AU_RepDocuSignInfobyRepIdESignatureUserGet
CALLING PROGRAM		: Rep Service 
INPUT PARAMETERS        : @username varchar(50)
OUTPUT PARAMETER        : NONE
CALLING SYNTAX		: exec  dbo.AU_RepDocuSignInfobyRepIdESignatureUserGet
DESCRIPTION			: return top 1 rep id, email address and docusignid with ActiveFlag 
                      equal 1 and StatusId equal 2
TIBCO PROCESS		:   
TIBCO SUB PROCESS	: 
MODIFICATION HISTORY:
=============================================================================
DATE		VERSION		MODIFIED BY		DESCRIPTION
=============================================================================
07/08/2022	1.0.0		Eva Adamovich		Initial Creation: MWOMSS-352
07/15/2022	1.0.1		Eva Adamovich		Initial Creation: MWOMSS-352 mistake found in the original spreadsheet
--and es.StatusId = 2   and ui.username = @username line was commented
****************************************************************************/
AS
BEGIN
 SET NOCOUNT ON;
 
		Select top 1 ui.RepId, es.EmailAddress as DocuSignEmailAddress, es.DocuSignId 
		From Auth.dbo.UserInfo ui
			inner join Auth.dbo.ESignatureUser es 
			 on ui.UserId = es.UserInfoId
		where  ui.ActiveFlag = 1 and es.StatusId = 2 
                and ui.username = @username 
 End
GRANT EXECUTE ON  dbo.AU_RepDocuSignInfobyRepIdESignatureUserGet TO PUBLIC
storedProcedure.name: AU_RepDocuSignInfobyRepIdESignatureUserGet

CREATE PROCEDURE [dbo].[usp_credit_ledger_insert] (
	@RepId VARCHAR(50) = NULL,
   @ContractId INT = NULL,
   @SubscriptionProductId INT = NULL,
   @ProductId INT = NULL,
   @PlanType VARCHAR(50) = NULL,
   @CreditBalance INT = NULL,
   @ContractStartDate DATETIME2 = NULL,
   @ContractEndDate DATETIME2 = NULL,
   @InsertType VARCHAR(50) = NULL
)
-- ===============================================================================
-- (c)2022 LPL Financial. All Rights Reserved.
-- Date: 2022-09-21
-- Author: Peter Avenarius
-- Summary: Inserts a new credit ledger
-- Example:
--    EXEC paraplanning.usp_credit_ledger_insert 'T2XA', 38628, 386, None, 0, '2022-08-30 00:00:00.0000000', '2023-02-28 00:00:00.0000000'
-- ===============================================================================
AS
BEGIN
	SET NOCOUNT ON;

   DECLARE @InsertLog table(
      [id] [INT] NOT NULL,
      [rep_id] [VARCHAR](50) NULL,
	   [sf_contract_id] [INT] NULL,
      [sf_subscription_product_id] [INT] NOT NULL,
      [sf_product_id] [INT] NOT NULL,
	   [plan_type] [VARCHAR](50) NULL,
	   [credit_balance] [INT] NULL,
      [contract_start_date] [DATETIME2] NULL,
      [contract_end_date] [DATETIME2] NULL,
	   [created_date] [DATETIME2] NULL,
	   [last_updated] [DATETIME2] NULL
      );

   DECLARE @CurrentDateTime DATETIME2 = SYSDATETIME();
   DECLARE @InsertSubscriptionProductId INT = NULL
   IF (@SubscriptionProductId IS NOT NULL)
      BEGIN
         SET @InsertSubscriptionProductId = @SubscriptionProductId
      END
   ELSE
      BEGIN
         SET @InsertSubscriptionProductId = @ProductId
      END

	INSERT INTO dbo.credit_ledger(rep_id, sf_contract_id, sf_subscription_product_id, sf_product_id, plan_type, credit_balance,
      contract_start_date, contract_end_date, created_date, last_updated)
   OUTPUT INSERTED.id, INSERTED.rep_id, INSERTED.sf_contract_id, INSERTED.sf_subscription_product_id, INSERTED.sf_product_id, INSERTED.plan_type, INSERTED.credit_balance,
      INSERTED.contract_start_date, INSERTED.contract_end_date, INSERTED.created_date, INSERTED.last_updated
   INTO @InsertLog
   VALUES(@RepId, @ContractId, @InsertSubscriptionProductId, @ProductId, @PlanType, @CreditBalance, @ContractStartDate, @ContractEndDate, @CurrentDateTime, @CurrentDateTime)

   -- insert record into credit ledger history table to track
   INSERT INTO dbo.credit_ledger_history(rep_id, contract_id, credit_balance, plan_type, update_type, source, user_id, created_date, last_updated)
   VALUES(@RepId, @ContractId, @CreditBalance, @PlanType, @InsertType, 'System', NULL, @CurrentDateTime, @CurrentDateTime);

   SELECT cl.id, cl.rep_id, cl.sf_contract_id, cl.sf_subscription_product_id, cl.sf_product_id, cl.plan_type,
      cl.credit_balance, cl.contract_start_date, cl.contract_end_date, 
      cl.created_date, cl.last_updated
   FROM @InsertLog cl
END
storedProcedure.name: usp_credit_ledger_insert
